<button id="myButton">Click me!</button>
<script>
  const button = document.getElementById('myButton');
  button.addEventListener('click', function() {
    console.log('Button clicked!');
  });
3. Programming Concepts

Understanding of:
Functional programming principles
Object-Oriented Programming (OOP) concepts
Event-driven programming
State and props management
4. Familiarity with Front-end Build Tools

Knowledge of:
npm (Node Package Manager) and yarn
Webpack or other module bundlers
Babel or other transpilers
CSS preprocessors like Sass or Less
5. Understanding of Web Development

Familiarity with:
Client-side rendering and server-side rendering
RESTful APIs and HTTP requests
Web storage and cookies
Browser compatibility and debugging techniques
6. Basic Understanding of React Ecosystem

Familiarity with:
JSX (JavaScript XML) syntax
React components, props, and state
React Hooks (useState, useEffect, etc.)
React Router or other client-side routing libraries
Optional but Recommended

Knowledge of:
TypeScript or other type systems
GraphQL or other data query languages
Redux or other state management libraries
WebAssembly or other emerging web technologies
